.TH TORAM-EJECT 1 "June 2026" "mx-remaster" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
toram-eject \- eject the live boot media after a successful toram boot
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B toram-eject
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B toram-eject
is a small helper for live systems booted with
.BR toram .
After the live system has been copied to RAM, the script checks that the boot
media is removable and no longer mounted, then offers to eject and optionally
close the optical drive.

This tool is normally launched automatically by the live workflow when the
.B toram
boot path succeeds.
.SH OPTIONS
.B toram-eject
does not define any tool-specific options.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /live/config/toram-eject
Flag file that triggers the eject workflow.
.TP
.I /live/config
Live configuration directory used to read the boot device.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR live-grubsave (1),
.BR eject (1)
.SH AUTHOR
mx-remaster maintainers
